Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with Expedia Group. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, cloud infrastructure, and AI systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and collaborative culture this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I applied software engineering principles and design patterns to architect an API integration layer translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution in production environments. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented comprehensive testing and monitoring infrastructure using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to debug applications and ensure production stability. I also built modular, maintainable code for developers through API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows, accelerating API integration and improving implementation correctness. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis with API access patterns that handled file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO in hybrid cloud infrastructure — giving me direct experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS in an agile team environment with version control, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications in production, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions, applying software design principles to prevent Lambda timeouts and ensure system reliability. Together, these roles have prepared me to collaborate with team members to co-develop solutions, apply database design principles, and contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities.

